methods.functionFromMapWithDefault:
Convert a map to a function.

:param map: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) - the map to convert to function; the caller gives up ownership to the returned object
:param defaultValue: (java.lang.String) - the value to map to any keys not in the map; may be null
:return: (java.util.function.Function<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) the resulting function
methods.functionFromMapWithIdentityDefaults:
Convert a map to a function, mapping any nonexistent keys in the map to themselves.

:param map: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) - the map to convert to function; the caller gives up ownership to the returned object
:return: (java.util.function.Function<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>) the resulting function

text: Functions to support interfacing to python from java
